subSubSection.paragraph:
Examples of morphological similarity between phylogenetically distant taxa are not rare among Emberizoids, and this is one of the reasons why classification in groups like tanagers, emberizids and cardinalids has been subject to extensive revision following molecular phylogenetic analyses (Burns et al. 2014, 2016; Klicka et al. 2014 ;
Barker et al. 2015
;
Remsen et al. 2016
). However, the similarity between
C. flavovirens
and true Cholorospingus that had thus far misled taxonomists who considered them congeneric represents a remarkable case of evolutionary convergence in plumage, morphology, and behavior between taxa belonging to different families.
